    "## Engineering context\n",
    "\n",
    "CO₂ transport systems can move from gas-like to dense-fluid behavior over a narrow\n",
    "pressure and temperature interval. Density controls line pack and velocity; heat\n",
    "capacity affects cooling duty and transient temperature; speed of sound affects\n",
    "pressure-wave propagation; viscosity affects friction; and phase or dry-ice formation\n",
    "can invalidate equipment assumptions.\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook is an educational screening workflow. It is not a custody-transfer\n",
    "standard, a pipeline design certificate, or a substitute for qualified experimental\n",
    "data in an impurity range outside a model's published validity."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "eb6bf47b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Governing thermodynamics\n",
    "\n",
    "The compressibility factor relates pressure, molar volume, and temperature:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "Z = \\frac{P V_m}{R T}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Density follows from molar mass $M$:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\rho = \\frac{P M}{Z R T}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "At low pressure, $Z$ approaches one and the ideal-gas density is a useful independent\n",
    "limit. Cubic equations of state such as SRK and Peng–Robinson calculate phase\n",
    "equilibrium efficiently. Span–Wagner is a high-accuracy Helmholtz-energy equation for\n",
    "pure CO₂. EOS-CG extends the Helmholtz framework to combustion and CCS mixtures.\n",
    "\n",
    "The dimensionless Helmholtz energy separates ideal and residual contributions:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\alpha = \\alpha^0 + \\alpha^r\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Here $P$ is absolute pressure in pascals, $V_m$ is molar volume in cubic metres per\n",
    "mole, $R$ is the gas constant in joules per mole-kelvin, $T$ is kelvin, $\\rho$ is\n",
    "kilograms per cubic metre, and $Z$ and $\\alpha$ are dimensionless."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "655f0173",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## How NeqSim represents the calculation\n",
    "\n",
    "- a thermodynamic `System` stores components, amount, temperature, pressure, model,\n",
    "  phase options, and property methods;\n",
    "- `TPflash` finds equilibrium at specified temperature and pressure;\n",
    "- phase objects expose density, heat capacities, speed of sound, and transport models;\n",
    "- `ThermodynamicOperations` calculates dew points, phase envelopes, and other flashes;\n",
    "- named process streams carry the same thermodynamic system into connected equipment;\n",
    "- `ProcessSystem.run()` executes units in flowsheet order.\n",
    "\n",
    "Model choice is an engineering decision. SRK and PR are efficient process models;\n",
    "Span–Wagner is preferred for high-accuracy pure CO₂; EOS-CG is intended for CO₂-rich\n",
    "CCS and combustion mixtures within its supported component set."
   ]
  },
