    "## Preserved example: PFCT viscosity\n",
    "\n",
    "Viscosity controls Reynolds number and frictional pressure loss. The original\n",
    "Pedersen friction-theory (`PFCT`) selection is retained. NeqSim initializes the\n",
    "physical-property package after the model is selected."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "2b9f7f61",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "CO₂ PFCT viscosity at 25 °C and 30 bara: 0.01656880 cP\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "base_srk.getPhase(\"gas\").getPhysicalProperties().setViscosityModel(\"PFCT\")\n",
    "base_srk.initPhysicalProperties()\n",
    "base_viscosity = base_srk.getViscosity(\"cP\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\n",
    "    \"CO₂ PFCT viscosity at 25 °C and 30 bara: \"\n",
    "    f\"{base_viscosity:.8f} cP\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "assert math.isfinite(base_viscosity)\n",
    "assert 0.01 < base_viscosity < 0.03"
   ]
  },
